[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating coverage issues**\n\nI’m considering how coverage depends on line numbers from a dynamic access report. The issue is that frames may appear as Unknown Source when there are no line numbers to indicate coverage. If the library jar lacks debug info, this could be why I’m encountering this. I wonder how previous tests managed coverage even when dealing with Unknown Source. The user is asking for improvements, so maybe I need to approach covering call sites more effectively.\n\n**Assessing coverage obstacles**\n\nI'm facing an issue where no active class remains in the jar, making it impossible to modify the library. There’s a thought about using a JCA provider, but it seems the private methods aren’t active. Could I adjust the test dependency to use a source with debug information? It doesn't seem right. Many BouncyCastle classes show Unknown Source and zero coverage. I'm wondering if I can create tests that trigger direct calls, but Unknown Source can’t generally be covered.\n\n**Exploring workaround options**\n\nI’m considering a potential workaround to get dynamic access call sites with line numbers. One idea is to create a test that uses dynamic access APIs from a subclass. However, the report shows that call sites come from native-image compilations without debug information, meaning coverage is impossible right now. The task still requires improvement, though. Maybe I can force coverage by adding a source file to shadow BCGOST3410PublicKey under test sources, while keeping tests outside library packages.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0769aab4046aa7850169fbeaaf3070819e8d24be1a4d71d94b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp--q8NGoPeGxTCtahYUhKwawdL0uIzwrkZdUt4erwjTPwT2MCa_bbFtup7BkGGWVeLSEgAg-VY1YANihk3eysV5Fdr8ZrcSsNRCR4bewcgSClxYI-iQkLjqLgoLlxNYr4mh2swwruFb6o_hhZzlby3OXwfftOXaE6BJLK7mmU1TsRifEW3_O3FYMndvLfwL16gX4nsxf